transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thanks for calling Viagra, this is Charles.

Speaker 2: Hello.

Speaker 1: Hey, how you doing?

Speaker 2: Yeah, oh, I've got a question for you.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: How do you get that new Viagra that you're selling?

Speaker 1: The AGV?

Speaker 2: Pardon me?

Speaker 1: The AGV?

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: That's what you ordered.

Speaker 2: Franklin Addison?

Speaker 1: Yeah, I got it.

Speaker 2: Just a minute.

Speaker 1: Is that the new Viagra that's good for after 11 minutes or something like that?

Speaker 2: Yeah, yeah.

Speaker 1: Yeah, it looks like you ordered 10 pills back on the 30th of December.

Speaker 2: Hang on just a minute.

Speaker 1: What the hell?

Speaker 2: Oh, there you are.

Speaker 1: Crap.

Speaker 2: Can't do anything today.

Speaker 1: In other words, this is the same as the one that you're saying it lasts, you know,

Speaker 2: after 11 or whatever, 11 minutes, I can't even talk today for some reason or another.

Speaker 1: It's okay.

Speaker 2: Yeah, so that pill that you have should have the number 100 pressed onto it like a stamp.

Speaker 1: And yes, that is the one that is supposed to activate within about 11 to 30 minutes.

Speaker 2: I tell everybody 30 minutes, Franklin, not going to lie.

Speaker 1: Everybody's body is built differently, so it should kick in within 11 to 30 minutes.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: What else did I ask?

Speaker 2: How do you take it?

Speaker 1: Just swallow it or let it dissolve under?

Speaker 2: No, swallow it with some water and then make sure you don't drink any alcohol and no heavy meals before it.

Speaker 1: I don't drink anyway, so I don't have to worry about that.

Speaker 2: Right.

Speaker 1: Okay, that's what I wanted to know because it didn't say.

Speaker 2: And I thought, well, I'm not going to take it until I find out.

Speaker 1: And I couldn't find anything to say or to call to find out.

Speaker 2: And then I happened to see this number said support, so I figured you'd know.

Speaker 1: Right, right.

Speaker 2: Very good.

Speaker 1: Yeah, if you ever need more, give us a call, okay?

Speaker 2: Do you need more actually?

Speaker 1: Not right now.

Speaker 2: I'm just waiting for whatever.

Speaker 1: It's going to happen in a couple of days.

Speaker 2: Gotcha.

Speaker 1: Okay, I'll make sure that we pause any refills from now until May.

Speaker 2: That way you've got some time to try them out and let us know when you need more, okay?

Speaker 1: I sure will.

Speaker 2: Thank you much.

Speaker 1: I appreciate it.

Speaker 2: Sounds good.

Speaker 1: Absolutely.

Speaker 2: Have a great day.

Speaker 1: All right, bye.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.
